  <p>A gurgle is air finding its way through the plumbing when water isn't flowing freely. On a septic system, that can be a small venting quirk — or an early hint that the system is backing up.</p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/what-causes-drains-to-gurgle-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
  <ResourceImageSlot
